definition.value: A monochlorobiphenyl carrying a single chloro substituent at position 2.
A C-nitro compound that is nitrobenzene in which one of the ortho- hydrogens has been replaced by chlorine.
A member of the class of toluenes carrying an ethyl group at the ortho-position.
A hydroxybenzophenone that is benzophenone which is substituted at the 2- and 4-positions of one of the benzene rings by hydroxy and methoxy groups respectively.
An enoate ester that is the monomethacryloyl derivative of ethylene glycol.
1,3-Benzothiazole substituted at the 2-position with a sulfanyl group.
A long chain fatty acid consisting of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid carrying a methoxy substituent at position 2; naturally occurring only in the phospholipids of sponges.
An acyl-CoA thioester that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-naphthoic acid..
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is decanoic acid carrying an oxo group at position 2.
A member of the class of phenols that is phenol carrying a butan-2-yl group at position 2.
A carbamate ester obtained by the formal condensation of 2-sec-butylphenol with methylcarbamic acid.
A HETE that consists of arachidonic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 20.
A 24-hydroxycholesterol that has S configuration at position 24. It is the major metabolic breakdown product of cholesterol in the brain.
A member of the class of rifamycins that is rifamycin SV lacking the O-methyl group at position 27.
A pentachlorobiphenyl in which the chlorines are located at the 3, 4, 5, 3', and 4' positions.
